President Obama announced his intent to nominate William C. Ostendorff for the position of Commissioner at the Nuclear Regulatory Commission. Ostendorff currently serves as a member of the Nuclear Regulatory Commission, a position he has held since April 2010. Prior to this, he worked as the Director of the Committee on Science, Engineering and Public Policy at the National Academies. He also served as the Principal Deputy Administrator at the National Nuclear Security Administration and worked on the staff of the House Armed Services Committee. Ostendorff had a distinguished career in the United States Navy, retiring as a Captain in 2002. He holds degrees in systems engineering, law, and an LLM from Georgetown University Law Center.